==English==

===Etymology===
Latin, from [[innumerabilis]]. See also French [[innumefable]]. Derived from [[in-]] prefix and [[numerable]].

===Adjective===
'''innumerable'''
#Not capable of being [[counted]], [[enumerated]], or [[numbered]], hence, indefinitely numerous; of great number.

===Synonyms===
*[[multitude]]
*[[countless]]
*[[numberless]]
*[[unnumbered]]

